Flames shot out of Thassalin's maw as the enormous Thrakian set a specific woodland area in bounds and then circled over it to detect movements.  Oddly, the eerie shrieking behind him fell silent as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's that supposed to be, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thrakos once!"
"When I fly myself, it's completely different from being suddenly lifted up by a huge pink dragon!"
"It wasn't that bad, was it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not Nyssis' opinion. He looked less black than otherwise and his claws had sunk so deep into Thassalins back that the Thracian was bleeding. Thassalin didn't seem to mind, however. Nevertheless, it had become clear to him that he had scared off his new friends, and landed on a clearing.
"I'm sorry, but I had burnt something. I had to worry about that!"
"But you had to drag us along with you too?", growled Tenuk, as he climbed off Thassalin's back and slid down onto his tail. "And we've left Retvik behind! Our big, strong fighter has been left in the lurch! How is he ever going to catch up to us?"
"He'll think of something, I'm sure...", growled Nyssi. "Retvik is not the fastest, but he's not stupid."
"Alright, but can Retvik drive?"
Nyssi blinked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen him drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I haven't seen him drive a nice small car like Kayel's either. Also, he only started taking the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle."
Echoes of loud laughter interrupted her. Thassalin suddenly seemed to find something utterly comical, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took a bit too long for Thassalin to calm down.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I PRESENTED YOUR MASSIVE FRIEND ALL DRESSED UP ON THIS TINY LITTLE BIKE FOR TEMTHAN KIDS. THAT WAS KILLING! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. A MAGNIFICENT IMAGINATION! ONE THAT I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, thinking he knew what was going on in Thassalin's head. "Yes, that's true. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, picked up, and disappeared. When he returned briefly, he threw something lifeless in front of Nyssi's feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, gold-white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR YOUR SHOUTS. SMELL YOUR BLOOD. SOMETHING DRIVES ME TO PROTECT AND HUNT. LIKE YISINI COMMANDS. THEY ARE VERY CLOSE."
The powerful Thracian froze suddenly. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and watched intently at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and snarled. Whatever it was, it spread two enormous wing pairs and shot at Thassalin, not bothering with the three smaller creatures between them. Kayel and Tenuk could just barely take cover, but Nyssi was swept up and almost flung at Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by snatching Nyssi and throwing him onto his back with his incredibly long and skillful tail, before launching himself into the air. The black, double-winged creature pursued them at high speed.
Kayel whistled irritably as he took down his rifle from his back and opened a pouch containing an ammunition belt. He hung the belt across his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thracian, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?", Kayel asked.
"Do you want to follow her?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a huge monster!"
"Yes and? I'm standing here with a high-caliber gun in my hand and could shoot it straight away. But, well, how shall I say – I would have to be able to see it first, so I could hit it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to have more space. With a soft, pained grunt, Tenuk's body stretched out, his fur turned to scales and his arms to wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, sky-blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Get on."
Like an ordinary Thracian, Tenuk now had a decent scaly shield running along his back. Conveniently, a pair of spines had also grown on his back that Kayel could hold onto. It took him a bit too long to get airborne, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to take up pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized they weren't alone. A second dark entity shot up underneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided a collision.
"That's probably the other terrifying giant monster that Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel furrowed his brow. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too busy focusing on the flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, although the other beast was following them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in sight. The fact that it was following them was a benefit for Kayel, as he could easily aim and shoot. Two shots went through the upper wings of the beast. It roared in pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it would definitely not be able to keep up with them.
A good piece ahead of them, Nyssi was desperately clinging, while Thassalin flailed about and spat flames at the blackened monster. The creature was definitely hurt. It seemed furiously angry, but not ready to give up. The fireballs seemed to have the desired effect. As Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi seized the opportunity to draw her own weapon, a good old shotgun. It wasn't necessarily the first choice, but maybe the buckshot would scare off the black beast.
